comments: Vucevic (CHI) firms up in a screening position in Anderson's (MIN) path and does not deliver contact.
Anderson (MIN) jumps from A to B into DeRozan's (CHI) body, dislodging him from his position when he controls the rebound.
Anderson (MIN) slightly extends his arms, but the contact with LaVine (CHI) is marginal before the two players engage.
Beverley (CHI) lifts and re-plants his pivot foot upon gathering the ball.
Vucevic (CHI) has a hand placed on Gobert's (MIN) waist but the marginal contact does not affect Gobert's ability to receive the pass.
Vucevic (CHI) initiates contact with Gobert's (MIN) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
DeRozan (CHI) does not fully establish himself in the frontcourt within eight seconds.
Beverley (CHI) gives a step of distance when establishing himself in McDaniels's (MIN) path and marginal contact occurs during the screen.
Anderson (MIN) reaches across DeRozan's (CHI) front, but the marginal contact does not affect his SQBR.

DeRozan (CHI) makes a natural basketball move towards the basket and contact occurs to Anderson's (MIN) face when he reaches in.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Gobert (MIN) jumps vertically and absorbs the ensuing contact with DeRozan (CHI) during his driving shot attempt.
LaVine (CHI) briefly brings his hand toward Anderson's (MIN) front and marginal contact occurs during Anderson's drive.
Anderson (MIN) brings both hands to the ball and resumes his dribble thereafter.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in McDaniels's (MIN) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
LaVine (CHI) engages with McDaniels (MIN) and marginal contact occurs as LaVine releases away to retrieve the pass.
Beverley (CHI) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Gobert (MIN) during his upward shooting motion.
Prince (MIN) reaches in and marginal contact occurs with DeRozan (CHI) that does not affect his SQBR.
Gobert (MIN) reaches in and makes contact with the ball, but his hand slides off the ball and makes contact to DeRozan's (CHI) right wrist that affects his driving shot attempt.
Conley (MIN) brings both hands to the ball and resumes his dribble thereafter.
Vucevic (CHI) absorbs the contact that occurs with McDaniels (MIN) during his driving shot attempt when his momentum carries him forward.
McDaniels (MIN) is the last player to touch ball before it goes out of bounds.
Reid (MIN) makes clean contact with the ball contesting LaVine's (CHI) dunk attempt and any ensuing contact is incidental.
Conley (MIN) firms up in LaVine's (CHI) path and marginal body contact occurs.

Reid (MIN) reaches for the rebound and marginal contact occurs with Beverley's (CHI) head as he secures the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Caruso (CHI) extends his arm forward and initiates contact that affects Reid's (MIN) control of the ball.
The Timberwolves are assessed a delay-of-game violation.
Beverley (CHI) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Alexander-Walker (MIN), which affects his play at the basket.
Alexander-Walker (MIN) is positioned inside the restricted area when contact occurs with Vucevic (CHI) during the dunk.
Anderson (MIN) initiates contact with DeRozan's (CHI) arm and affects DeRozan's SQBR.
Reid (MIN) commits a take foul on DeRozan (CHI).
